{"word":"ἠλεός","slug":"ἠλεός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἠλεός</b></el> <el>(ἠλεός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀλάομαι'><el>ἀλάομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>astray, distraught, crazed</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; also in apocop. form <el>ἠλέ</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <el>ἠλεά</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>foolishly</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>distracting, crazing</i>, <el>οἶνος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}